76. Johnson e Wichern - ExercÃ­cio 12.3.

Sabemos que o \(r\) (correlacao) pode ser obtido por meio da seguinte formula:

\[ r = \frac{\sum (x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y})}{\sqrt{\sum (x_i-\bar{x})^2(y_i-\bar{y})^2}} \]

Sabemos que:

\[ \bar{x} = \frac{a+b}{p} \ \ \ \ \ \ \bar{y} = \frac{a+c}{p} \] \[ x_1 = a+b \ \ \ \ \ \ \ x_2 = b+c \] \[ y_1 = a+c \ \ \ \ \ \ \ y_2 = b+d \] onde \(p\) Ã© o total:

\[ p = a+b+c+d \]

Agora vamos encontrar os seguintes resultados:

\[ \sum (x_i-\bar{x})^2 = (a+b)(1-\frac{a+b}{p})^2 + (c+d)(0-\frac{a+b}{p})^2 = \frac{(a+b)+(c+d)}{p} \] \[ \sum (x_i-\bar{x})^2 = (a+c)(1-\frac{a+c}{p})^2 + (b+d)(0-\frac{a+c}{p})^2 = \frac{(a+c)+(b+d)}{p} \] \[ \sum (x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y}) = \sum (x_iy_i-y_i\bar{x}-x_i\bar{y}+\bar{x}\bar{y}) \] \[ \sum (x_iy_i-y_i\bar{x}-x_i\bar{y}+\bar{x}\bar{y}) = a + \frac{(a+c)+(a+b)}{p} - \\ \frac{(a+b)+(a+c)}{p} + p \frac{(a+b)+(a+c)}{p^2} + \\ \frac{a(a+b+c+d)-(a+c)(a+b)}{p} = \frac{ad-bc}{p} \]

Com isso podemos chegar:

\[ r = \frac{\sum (x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y})}{\sqrt{\sum (x_i-\bar{x})^2(y_i-\bar{y})^2}} = \frac{\frac{ad-bc}{p}}{\sqrt{(\frac{(a+b)+(c+d)}{p})(\frac{(a+c)+(b+d)}{p})}} \] \[ r = \frac{\frac{ad-bc}{p}}{\sqrt{(\frac{(a+b)+(c+d)}{p})(\frac{(a+c)+(b+d)}{p})}} = \frac{\frac{ad-bc}{p}}{(\frac{(a+b)+(c+d)+(a+c)+(b+d)}{p^2})} \] \[ r = \frac{\frac{ad-bc}{p}}{(\frac{(a+b)+(c+d)+(a+c)+(b+d)}{p^2})} = \frac{ad-bc}{[(a+b)+(c+d)+(a+c)+(b+d)]^{1/2}} \]
